tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control, suggestive of prediabetes or diabetes. Creatinine is mildly elevated, which may reflect reduced renal function. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, urea, and calcium, are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and glycemic management.
